'''聯覺'''（{{lang-en|Synesthesia}}），又譯為'''共感覺'''、'''通感'''或'''聯感'''，是一種感覺現象，指其中一種感覺或認知途徑的刺激，導致第二種感覺或認知途徑的非自願經歷<ref name="isbn0-262-03296-1">{{page needed|date=January 2014}} {{cite book |first=Richard E. |last=Cytowic |title=Synesthesia: A Union of the Senses |publisher=[[MIT_Press|MIT Press]] |location=[[Cambridge,_Massachusetts|Cambridge, Massachusetts]] |year=2002 |pages= |isbn=978-0-262-03296-4 |oclc=49395033|edition=2nd }}</ref><ref name="isbn0-262-53255-7">{{page needed|date=January 2014}} {{cite book |first=Richard E. |last=Cytowic |title=The Man Who Tasted Shapes |url=https://archive.org/details/manwhotastedshap0000cyto_p4c2 |publisher=[[MIT_Press|MIT Press]] |location=[[Cambridge,_Massachusetts|Cambridge, Massachusetts]] |year=2003 |pages= |isbn=978-0-262-53255-6 |oclc=53186027}}</ref><ref name="Cytowic_Eagleman2009">{{page needed|date=January 2014}}{{cite book|author1=Cytowic, Richard E |author2=Eagleman, David M |title=Wednesday is Indigo Blue: Discovering the Brain of Synesthesia (with an afterword by Dmitri Nabokov)|publisher=[[MIT_Press|MIT Press]] |location=Cambridge |year=2009 |isbn=978-0-262-01279-9}}</ref><ref name="isbn0-631-19764-8">{{page needed|date=January 2014}} {{cite book |first=John E. |last=Harrison |author2=Simon Baron-Cohen  |title=Synaesthesia: classic and contemporary readings |publisher=[[Blackwell_Publishing|Blackwell Publishing]] |location=[[Oxford|Oxford]] |year=1996 |pages= |isbn=978-0-631-19764-5 |oclc=59664610|author2-link=Simon Baron-Cohen }}</ref>。聯覺感知的意識因人而異<ref name="campen2009">Campen, Cretien van (2009) "The Hidden Sense: On Becoming Aware of Synesthesia" TECCOGS, vol. 1, pp. 1–13.{{cite web|url=http://www.pucsp.br/pos/tidd/teccogs/artigos/pdf/teccogs_edicao1_2009_artigo_CAMPEN.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-02-18 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090708013028/http://www.pucsp.br/pos/tidd/teccogs/artigos/pdf/teccogs_edicao1_2009_artigo_CAMPEN.pdf |archivedate=2009-07-08 }}</ref>。在一種普遍的聯覺形式中，被稱為「{{le|字位→顏色聯覺|Grapheme–color synesthesia}}」或「顏色-字素聯覺」，當中[[字母|字母]]及[[數字|數字]]被認為具固有顏色<ref name="pmid11823804">{{cite journal|vauthors=Rich AN, Mattingley JB|date=January 2002|title=Anomalous perception in synesthesia: a cognitive neuroscience perspective|journal=[[Nature_Reviews_Neuroscience|Nature Reviews Neuroscience]]|type=Review|volume=3|issue=1|pages=43–52|doi=10.1038/nrn702|pmid=11823804}}</ref><ref name="pmid16269367">{{cite journal|vauthors=Hubbard EM, Ramachandran VS|date=November 2005|title=Neurocognitive mechanisms of synesthesia|journal=Neuron|type=Review|volume=48|issue=3|pages=509–20|doi=10.1016/j.neuron.2005.10.012|pmid=16269367}}</ref>。在空間序列或{{le|數字形式|Number form}}的聯覺中，數字、一年中的月份、一周中的日子會在空間中確定精確位置（例如，1980年可能比1990年「更遠」），或可能顯示為三維地圖（順時針或逆時針）<ref name="galton1880b">{{cite journal|author=Galton F|year=1880|title=Visualized Numerals|url=https://zenodo.org/record/1429243|journal=Nature|volume=21|issue=543|pages=494–5|doi=10.1038/021494e0|pmid=|bibcode=1880Natur..21..494G|access-date=2020-05-26|archive-date=2019-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190701204433/https://zenodo.org/record/1429243|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="pmid1511585">{{cite journal|vauthors=Seron X, Pesenti M, Noël MP, Deloche G, Cornet JA|date=August 1992|title=Images of numbers, or "When 98 is upper left and 6 sky blue"|journal=Cognition|volume=44|issue=1–2|pages=159–96|doi=10.1016/0010-0277(92)90053-K|pmid=1511585}}</ref>。聯覺的聯想可能發生於任何數量的感官或認知途徑的任意組合<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://science.howstuffworks.com/life/inside-the-mind/emotions/synesthesia1.htm|title=How Synesthesia Works|date=1970-01-01|website=HowStuffWorks|access-date=2016-05-02|archive-date=2020-02-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200212232633/https://science.howstuffworks.com/life/inside-the-mind/emotions/synesthesia1.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

<!-- 成因 -->
關於聯覺如何發展所知甚少。有人提出，兒童於兒時首次深入接觸抽象概念時，就會發展出聯覺<ref name="MroczkoNikolic2014" />。這個假設稱為「語義真空假設（semantic vacuum hypothesis）」，這解釋為何聯覺最常見的形式是字素色、空間序列和數字形式。這些通常是教育系統要求兒童學習的第一種抽象概念。

<!-- 診斷 -->
在充分定義聯覺方面存在著困難<ref name="ideasthesia">{{cite journal |author=Nikolić D |title=Is synaesthesia actually ideaesthesia? An inquiry into the nature of the phenomenon |journal=Proceedings of the Third International Congress on Synaesthesia, Science & Art, Granada, Spain, April 26–29 |year=2009 |url=http://www.danko-nikolic.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Synesthesia2009-Nikolic-Ideaesthesia.pdf |access-date=2020-05-26 |archive-date=2019-07-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190712210332/http://www.danko-nikolic.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Synesthesia2009-Nikolic-Ideaesthesia.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="defsyn">{{cite journal |author=Simner J |title=Defining synaesthesia |journal=British Journal of Psychology |volume=103 |issue=6 |pages=1–15 |year=2012 |doi=10.1348/000712610X528305 |pmid=22229768 |type=Review |url=https://www.pure.ed.ac.uk/ws/files/12435588/Defining_synaesthesia.pdf |access-date=2020-05-26 |archive-date=2019-07-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190709165250/https://www.pure.ed.ac.uk/ws/files/12435588/Defining_synaesthesia.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。聯覺一詞已包括許多不同的現象（感官聯盟）在內，並且在許多情況下，該術語似乎不準確。一個更準確但不太常見的術語可能是「{{le|抽象概念引發的感覺|Ideasthesia}}」。

<!-- 歷史 -->
最早記錄的聯覺事件歸功於英國[[牛津大學|牛津大學]]學術與哲學家[[约翰·洛克|約翰·洛克]]，他於1690年發表了一篇關於一名盲人的報告，該盲人說當他聽到[[小號|小號]]的聲音時就經歷了猩紅色<ref name=OssianWard>Ward, Ossian (10 June 2006) [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/art/3653012/The-man-who-heard-his-paintbox-hiss.html The man who heard his paint box hiss] {{Wayback|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/art/3653012/The-man-who-heard-his-paintbox-hiss.html |date=20190701202435 }} in [[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Telegraph]]. Retrieved 3 December 2018</ref>。然而，對於洛克所描述之聯覺的實際情況還是使用了[[隱喻|隱喻]]存在著分歧<ref name=":2">{{Cite journal|last=Jewanski|first=Jörg|last2=Day|first2=Sean A.|last3=Ward|first3=Jamie|date=2009|title=A Colorful Albino: The First Documented Case of Synaesthesia, by Georg Tobias Ludwig Sachs in 1812|journal=Journal of the History of the Neurosciences: Basic and Clinical Perspectives|volume=18|issue=3|pages=293–303|doi=10.1080/09647040802431946|pmid=20183209|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/41563417|access-date=2020-05-26|archive-date=2020-02-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200212232715/https://www.researchgate.net/publication/41563417|dead-url=no}}</ref>。首個醫療記錄來自德國醫生喬治·托比亞斯·路德維希·薩克斯（Georg Tobias Ludwig Sachs）於1812年的記錄<ref name=":2" /><ref name=":3">{{Cite web|url=https://www.britannica.com/science/synesthesia|title=Synesthesia|last=Herman|first=Laura M.|date=2018-12-28|website=Encyclopaedia Britannica|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190729165118/https://www.britannica.com/science/synesthesia|archive-date=2019-07-29|url-status=|access-date=2019-01-25|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogs.scientificamerican.com/literally-psyched/from-the-words-of-an-albino-a-brilliant-blend-of-color/|title=From the words of an albino, a brilliant blend of color|last=Konnikova|first=Maria|date=2013-02-26|website=Scientific American|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920114035/https://blogs.scientificamerican.com/literally-psyched/from-the-words-of-an-albino-a-brilliant-blend-of-color/|archive-date=2016-09-20|url-status=|access-date=2019-01-25}}</ref>。

「聯覺」一詞源於[[古希臘語|古希臘語]] {{polytonic|[[wikt:σύν|σύν]]}}（意為「共同」）和{{polytonic|[[wikt:αἴσθησις|αἴσθησις]]}}（意為「aisthēsis，[[wikt:感觉|感觉]]」）。其解釋為一種具有神經基礎的感知狀態，表示一種感官刺激或認知途徑會自發且非主動地引起另一種感知或認識<ref name="isbn0-262-03296-1" /><ref name="isbn0-262-53255-7" /><ref name="Cytowic_Eagleman2009" />。真正的聯覺是無意識的，文學修辭手法中的[[通感|通感]]（如「苦澀的風」或「尖利的笑聲」等），有時也會被描述為「聯覺的」。據估算平均每23個人中便有1人擁有某種聯覺<ref name="pmid17076063">{{cite journal |author=Simner J, Mulvenna C, Sagiv N, ''et al.'' |title=Synaesthesia: the prevalence of atypical cross-modal experiences |journal=Perception |volume=35 |issue=8 |pages=1024–33 |year=2006 |pmid=17076063 |doi= 10.1068/p5469|url=}}</ref>。報告此類經歷的終身歷史的人通常被稱為「'''聯覺者'''（{{lang-en|synesthete}}）」。他們對聯覺的感受很少發生改變，例如一個人「感到」數字１是紅色的，當他每次看到數字１時，都會「看見」紅色。當問及聯覺者怎麼發現自己的聯覺時，他們並不會認為自己的體驗不尋常，直至他們意識到自己有別於其他人。有些聯覺者會感到整個生活都在保守這秘密<ref name="campen2007">{{cite book |last=van Campen |first=Cretien |year=2007 |title=The Hidden Sense: Synesthesia in Art and Science |url=https://archive.org/details/hiddensensesynes0000camp |location=Cambridge, Massachusetts |publisher=[[MIT_Press|MIT Press]] |isbn=0-262-22081-4 |oclc=80179991 |language=en }}</ref>。

== 機制 ==
